{{Quote|I have dedicated my entire life to serving this [[United States|country]]. The one person that matters... doesn't seem to understand. [[Betty Ross|Betty]] never forgave me for [[Bruce Banner Manhunt|sending]] the [[United States Army|Army]] after [[Bruce Banner|Banner]]. I had to survive... so that my daughter knew that there was more to her father. That I'm the same man that used to take her to see the cherry blossoms.|Thaddeus Ross to [[Sam Wilson]]|Captain America: Brave New World}}
'''Thaddeus E. "Thunderbolt" Ross''' is a former President of the [[United States]], a former Lieutenant General in the [[United States Army]], and a former Secretary of State under President [[Matthew Ellis]]' administration. During his career, he was put in charge of [[Project Gamma Pulse]], with Ross' goal being to recreate the [[Super Soldier Serum]]. However, the experiment led to an accident which then transformed the scientist [[Bruce Banner]] into [[Hulk]]. Following a [[Bruce Banner Manhunt|long chase]], Banner got recaptured, only for [[Emil Blonsky]] to use all their experiments to transform into the Abomination. In the face of these odds, Ross was forced to accept Hulk as an ally, allowing him to escape after the [[Duel of Harlem|fight]] in [[New York City]], while Ross had been left humiliated. Afterwards, Ross had [[Samuel Sterns]] take the fall for the incident, imprisoned him at [[Camp Echo One]], and exposed him to gamma radiation in order to further heighten his intelligence and subsequently forced him to work on new ideas.

Ross would leave the military and pursue a political career, being appointed the {{WPS|United States Secretary of State}} during [[Matthew Ellis]]' administration. During this time, Ross had approved of the [[Sokovia Accords]], which aimed to control the actions of enhanced individuals, primarily the [[Avengers]]. When [[Steve Rogers]] publicly disowned the accords before going on the run, along with [[Bucky Barnes]], Ross instructed [[Tony Stark]] to bring them into custody. Ross arrested many of the Avengers, although Rogers would later break them out following the arrest of [[Helmut Zemo]]. Ross would also lead a manhunt for [[Natasha Romanoff]], although later deciding to turn a blind eye after she took down the [[Red Room]] and had ended [[Dreykov]]'s plans.

Ross' actions resulted in the divided Avengers failing to stop [[Thanos]] from causing the [[Snap]], killing half of all life, including Ross himself. Being resurrected in the [[Blip]], Ross attended [[Tony Stark]]'s funeral. In the years following, Ross’ health began to decline, and his heart problems became life-threatening. Desperate, Ross tasked Sterns with saving his life in exchange for his freedom, conditional that he also helped Ross secure the presidency. His impending death also made him begin to reflect on his life, including his strained relationship with his daughter [[Betty Ross|Betty]], his treatment of superheroes, and whether or not he could become a better person. Sterns ultimately developed pills laced with [[gamma radiation]] to stabilize Ross' heart failure.

In [[2026]], Ross was elected {{WPS|President of the United States}}, and charged with negotiating a [[Ozaki-Ross Accords|global treaty]] over [[adamantium]] on [[Tiamut the Communicator|Celestial Island]]. Ross broke his promise to free Sterns, prompting Sterns to become Leader and seek revenge. Leader's interference led to a [[Attack on President Ross|failed attempt]] on Ross' life at the [[White House]], and later [[Battle of Celestial Island|escalated tensions]] between the United States and [[Japan]] over adamantium, although conflict was averted by [[Captain America]]. As revenge, Leader activated the latent gamma radiation in Ross' system to trigger his transformation into '''Red Hulk''' at a press conference. Overcome with rage, Red Hulk [[Duel of Washington, D.C.|fought]] Captain America but was ultimately talked down. Accepting responsibility, he resigned from office and surrendered to the [[Raft]], proving his capacity to change. While imprisoned, he finally reunited with Betty face-to-face.

==Biography==
{{MD|Thaddeus Ross (Earth-199999)}}
===Early Life===
====Creating Super Soldiers====
{{Quote|We've got an Infantry Weapons Development program. In [[World War II|WWII]], they initiated the [[Project Rebirth|sub-program]] for [[Super Soldier Serum|Bio-Tech Force Enhancement]]."<br>"Yeah, Super Soldier."<br>"Yes. An oversimplification, but yes. And I dusted it off, got 'em doing serious work again.|Thaddeus Ross and [[Emil Blonsky]]|The Incredible Hulk}}
Thaddeus Ross was born on [[1945|August 22, 1945]].{{Ref|CABNW}} In his adulthood, Thaddeus joined the [[United States Army]] and served during the {{WPS|Vietnam War}}, until he returned to the [[United States]] at age twenty-seven. Around this time Thaddeus married a woman named [[Karen Lee Ross|Karen Lee]], and in [[1973]] had a daughter named [[Betty Ross|Elizabeth]], or "Betty" for short, although they had a tense relationship.{{Ref|TIH}} Thaddeus lost his wife when she died on [[1993|July 21, 1993]], causing further division between him and his twenty year old daughter.{{Ref|CABNW}} Retaining a military career, Thaddeus rose through their ranks, becoming a three-star general. By the [[2000s]], he became involved in a research and development program intended to recreate the [[Super Soldier Serum]],{{Ref|TIH}} known as [[Project Gamma Pulse]].{{Ref|MSTMCUAOT}}

===Creating Hulk===
====Experiments Gone Wrong====
[[File:Hulk attacks Ross.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross sees [[Bruce Banner]] turning into [[Hulk]]]]
{{Quote|Across the hall, they were trying to arm you better. We were trying to make you better. [[Bruce Banner|Banner]]'s work was very early phase. It wasn't even weapons application. He thought that he was working on radiation resistance. I would never have told him [[Super Soldier Serum|what]] the project really was.|Thaddeus Ross to [[Emil Blonsky]]|The Incredible Hulk}}
By [[2005]], General Thaddeus Ross had made an agreement with the scientist [[Bruce Banner]], the boyfriend of his [[Betty Ross|daughter]], for working on his government project to the weapon development project, under the guise of it being used to render soldiers resistant to radiation, as Thaddeus did not intend to inform Banner of the experiment's meaning. Involved from early phase research, Banner conducted one test on himself dealing with [[gamma radiation]], instead of [[Vita Radiation|vita radiation]], being also administered with a myostatin primer developed by Betty, confident it would work.
[[File:General-Ross-Protects-Betty-Ross.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Thaddeus protecting [[Betty Ross]] from [[Hulk]]]]
However, as the experiment began, Thaddeus saw something go wrong as Banner was struck by an immense dosage of gamma radiation, causing an explosion. Following the blast, Banner was transformed into [[Hulk]], a giant and amazingly strong brute fueled by rage who fled after injuring his daughter, leaving her in a coma as well as killing two scientists, a soldier of the [[United States Army]] and also crushing Thaddeus' left arm.
[[File:General-Ross-confronts-Banner-prologe.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross furiously confronting [[Bruce Banner]]]] 
Thaddeus was left with a badly broken arm following the incident, as well as a deep hatred of Banner, whom he blamed for the entire incident which had almost killed his daughter. When Banner had transformed back to normal and returned in order to visit Betty while she was still recovering from her injuries in the hospital, Thaddeus was furious and threw out Banner who had to go on the run from the General.
[[File:GeneralRoss-FlashbackScene.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross ordering [[Bruce Banner]] to be captured]]
Taken by a sense of guilt and rage, Thaddeus put his life into the service of a single cause: to hunt down and capture Bruce Banner. Thaddeus took charge of the [[Strategic Operations Command Center]], focused on recovering the fugitive while in coordination with [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]], working along with [[Nick Fury]]. Thaddeus' obsession caused a rift between him and [[Betty Ross]], as she loved Banner. Their relationship never recovered from this.{{Ref|TIH}}

====Meeting with Tony Stark====
[[File:GeneralRoss-MapWatching.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross returning to his work as General]]
{{Quote|I know you've been distancing yourself from your [[Howard Stark|father]]'s legacy; you claim you're no longer a weapons maker; but now you are the weapon!|Thaddeus Ross to [[Tony Stark]]|Iron Man 2: Public Identity}}
Five years following the fatal "[[Hulk]] incident," as [[Tony Stark]] had become a superhero known as Iron Man, Senator [[Stern]] called up Ross as he took a break from his experiments.{{Ref|IM2PI1}} Together, they worked with [[Justin Hammer]] who presented to [[James Rhodes]] and Ross the [[Aerodynamic Marvel]], which he considered to be the next step in close-quarter combat with protection and to attack capabilities. Ross had secretly planned to use the vehicle in the place of Iron Man for the military's missions.
[[File:GeneralRoss-BreathingSmoke.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross continues searching for [[Bruce Banner]]]]
However, the machine was [[Attack on the Aerodynamic Marvel|shot down]] during testing in the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]].{{Ref|IM2PI2}} When Iron Man was sent in to clean up, Ross held off on an official rescue to witness him in action. Once Iron Man saved the pilot, Ross told him to land on [[Cairo]]'s [[Cairo West Air Base|West Air Base]]. There, he confronted Stark over not returning fire against the [[Congolese Army]]. Ross claimed that Stark was a weapon, despite distancing himself from his [[Howard Stark|father]]. Stark warned that if Ross put innocent lives in harm's way, there would be consequences.{{Ref|IM2PI3}}

===[[Bruce Banner Manhunt|Chase of Hulk]]===
====Building an Elite Team====
[[File:General-Ross-Learns-of-Banners-Location.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross getting updates from [[Kathleen Sparr]]]]
{{Quote|Your target is a [[Bruce Banner|fugitive]] from the {{WPS|United States Government|U.S. government}} who stole military secrets. He is implicated in the deaths of two scientists, a military officer, an [[Idaho (State)|Idaho]] state trooper and possibly two [[Canada|Canadian]] hunters. So don't wait to see if he's a fighter. Tranq him and bring him back.|Thaddeus Ross to [[Emil Blonsky]]|The Incredible Hulk}}
In [[2010|May 2010]], while working in the [[Pentagon]] in [[Virginia]], Ross was met by [[Kathleen Sparr]] who had received intel that a [[Watcher Informant|man]] in [[Milwaukee]] had received a strong case of [[Gamma Radiation|gamma poisoning]] after he had drunk a single bottle of [[Pingo Doce]]. Looking at that amount of gamma radiation which had been inside the drink, Ross deduced that this must have been caused by [[Bruce Banner]], who must have infected the bottle.
[[File:GeneralRoss-CloseUp-FindingBBanner.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross learns of [[Bruce Banner]]'s whereabouts]]
Having finally gained his first lead on Banner's location in years, Ross had immediately begun a frantic search for his target, ordering Sparr to track down this factory that had produced that soda, as she had explained was in [[Rocinha]], in [[Porto Verde]]. Ross ordered his soldiers and their contacts to look out for a white man who had been working in the factory while noting that the soldiers were not to make any contact with Banner as he would run at the first sign of danger.
[[File:General-Ross-Joe-Greer.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross and [[Joe Greller]] build his military unit]]
Believing that he was quickly closing in on capturing Banner at long last, Ross had begun putting together a special unit of highly trained soldiers with their sole purpose being to locate and capture Banner. Once he recruited the help of General [[Joe Greller]], Ross not only put together a team of some of the best soldiers he could find, as Greller also managed to hire one of the best operatives at his disposal, [[Emil Blonsky]], and had then sent them to the village of Porto Verde.
[[File:GeneralRoss-UnitBriefAboutBanner.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross briefs unit about [[Bruce Banner]]'s past]]
As they traveled to the location, Ross chooses to not disclose the secrets of Banner's condition, believing them to still be top-secret. He told Blonsky and the other soldiers that Banner was a target of the United States government who had stolen military secrets and when Blonsky asked for more details, he refused to share them. He ordered them to ensure that Banner was captured without incident, while not telling them of the risks involved with their mission.{{Ref|TIH}}

====Encounter in Brazil====
[[File:GeneralRoss-WatchingMonitor.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross watches [[Emil Blonsky]]'s team's actions]]
{{Quote|We got a [[Hulk|bogey]] of some kind. Please advise."<br>"That is the target! Use every tranq you've got. Do it now!|[[List of Minor Characters/Phase One#The Incredible Hulk|Soldier]] and Thaddeus Ross|The Incredible Hulk}}
Upon their arrival in [[Brazil]], Ross remained inside their armored van with [[Kathleen Sparr]] while [[Emil Blonsky]] led their team of soldiers to the location of [[Bruce Banner]]. Ross watched the monitors closely as their team arrived at the location before Ross gave the order and they blasted open the door and shot their darts at Banner, only to discover that Banner had already managed to make his escape.
[[File:General-Ross-sees-Bruce-Banner.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross finally catches up with [[Bruce Banner]]]]
Ross furiously ordered Blonsky and their team to find Banner, as they headed out onto the streets of [[Porto Verde]] until Blonsky managed to catch sight of their target and gave chase. Upon seeing this, Ross ordered his soldiers to drive him to Banner's location, with Ross still ordering Blonsky not to lose sight of Banner. As the [[Bruce Banner Manhunt|chase]] continued, Ross' truck eventually pulled up right in front of Banner, as Ross then stepped out to look at his target in the eyes before Banner fled.
[[File:RossToTeam-ThatIsTheTarget.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross witnesses Banner turning into [[Hulk]]]]
As the chase had continued, Blonsky's men then tracked Banner into a [[Pingo Doce Bottling Plant|factory]], while Ross pulled up outside and watched from the team's body cams as they silently entered the factory, finding Banner in the middle of his confrontation with some [[Silva (Pingo Doce)|tough guys]]. Just as Blonsky's men had him cornered, Ross watched in horror as Banner began his transformation into [[Hulk]], brutally dispatching the thugs who were trying to beat him up, as Ross ordered them to shoot at Hulk.
[[File:RossLosesTheHulkOnceAgain.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross watches as [[Hulk]] escapes him again]]
However, the team were incredibly underprepared for their encounter with Hulk, as they were all picked off, one by one, by the beast's incredible strength, as their tranquilizer darts simply bounced off his skin, much to Ross' horror. Eventually, only Blonsky was left alone to challenge Hulk, as he witnessed the beast throw a forklift truck at him, before smashing his way through a wall and escaping, as Ross yelled out in complete frustration as he lost his target once again.{{Ref|TIH}}

====Mission Aftermath====
[[File:RossBlonsky-PostBrazilChase.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross and Blonsky return to Banner's home]]
{{Quote|That was [[Bruce Banner|Banner]]. It was Banner."<br>"You have to explain that statement, sir."<br>"No, I don't. You've done a good job. Pack up and get our men on a plane. We're going home.|Thaddeus Ross and [[Emil Blonsky]]|The Incredible Hulk}}
In the wake of [[Bruce Banner]]'s escape, Ross and [[Kathleen Sparr]] had regrouped with [[Emil Blonsky]] at Banner's apartment to discuss the situation. Blonsky had presented Ross with the backpack that Banner had dropped during the chase, which included his laptop which Sparr began looking over. Blonsky noticed a picture of [[Betty Ross]] on the laptop, questioning who she was as Thaddeus refused to answer him, while he claimed that Betty was no longer a concern, insisting that Banner worked alone.
[[File:TRoss-ThatWasBanner.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross is asked about [[Bruce Banner]]'s power]]
While Ross then ordered Sparr to find out if Banner had been talking with [[Samuel Sterns|anybody]] else, Blonsky finally spoke up as he questioned if they were willing to talk about what happened back at the factory. Ross then listened while Blonsky insisted that Banner had not been alone, referring to [[Hulk]], with Blonsky insisting that their team had been attacked by something huge which was protecting Banner, furiously explaining how Hulk had thrown a forklift truck directly at him.
[[File:TRoss-PostBrazilChase.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross considers losing [[Bruce Banner]] again]]
Ross then spoke up, telling Blonsky that Hulk was gone and that it was Banner. As Blonsky had asked Ross to explain this statement, Ross refused to go into any more detail about how Banner had been able to transform himself into Hulk, much to Blonsky's frustration. Ross then ordered Blonsky and Sparr to collect the rest of their unit and return to the [[United States of America]], as Ross looked out over Brazil, believing he had lost his last chance to capture Banner.{{Ref|TIH}}

====Flight Home====
[[File:GeneralRoss-DeletedScene-PlaneRide1.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross looks at the reports on [[Bruce Banner]]]]
{{Quote|[[Bruce Banner|He]] wants to neutralize whatever powers the transformation."<br>"That's not a good thing."<br>"No, it's not a good thing, Major. But I don't want Banner anyway. God damn it! I want what's inside of him!|Thaddeus Ross and [[Kathleen Sparr]]|The Incredible Hulk - Deleted Scene}}
Following the disastrous mission in [[Brazil]], Ross took the bodies of the members of the [[Strategic Operations Command Center]] who had been killed in action as they flew back towards the [[United States]]. As Ross stood by the bodies of their soldiers, he listened while [[Kathleen Sparr]] had then explained to him exactly how [[Bruce Banner]] had managed to avoid any detection for so long.
[[File:GeneralRoss-DeletedScene-PlaneRide2-Yelling.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross furiously explaining his need for [[Hulk]]]]
Looking over all of the evidence that they had recovered, Ross finally deduced that Banner had been attempting to figure out a way to cure himself of [[Hulk]]. Sparr questioned if this was a good thing or not, as Ross furiously insisted that he had no interest in getting Banner, but that he wanted Hulk that was inside of him, as he could be a major asset to the [[United States Armed Forces]], while Sparr promised that they would still continue their search for Banner regardless.
[[File:GeneralRoss-DeletedScene-PlaneRide3.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross briefly locking eyes with [[Emil Blonsky]]]]
However, the infuriated Ross complained that this would be no use, as Banner was already on the move and he had proved himself more than capable of avoiding detection whenever he wanted to. As Ross paced around the plane, he locked eyes with [[Emil Blonsky]], who was still considering everything that he had witnessed during their clash with Hulk, as Ross and Blonsky looked at each other before Ross simply walked away without either saying a word to the other.{{Ref|TIHDS}}

====Updating General Greller====
[[File:GeneralRoss-DeletedScene-GrellerMeeting3.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross explains their situation to [[Joe Greller]]]]
{{Quote|Joe, what we are talking about here is [[Hulk|something]] that could be an incredibly dangerous weapon in the wrong hands, and we don't know what his intentions are."<br>"Put together a new list, but be prepared to explain everything on it.|Thaddeus Ross and [[Joe Greller]]|The Incredible Hulk - Deleted Scene}}
Once he had returned to the [[United States]], Ross went to meet with General [[Joe Greller]] to explain exactly what had happened in [[Brazil]] and how their men had been killed in action, with Ross then telling Greller exactly how [[Bruce Banner]] had transformed into [[Hulk]] and killed their men. Unsurprisingly, Greller was unconvinced by the story, although Ross insisted that he was being serious.
[[File:GeneralRoss-DeletedScene-GrellerMeeting2.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross bringing [[Emil Blonsky]] to their meeting]]
For confirmation of the story, Greller then invited [[Emil Blonsky]] in their meeting, who confirmed what Ross had already told Greller, detailing what his own [[Ambush in Porto Verde|battle]] against Hulk had been like. As Blonsky had finished his explanation, Greller demanded that Ross explain exactly what was going on with this mission, as Ross admitted that Banner had worked on a [[Project Gamma Pulse|Biotech Project]], to which Greller questioned if all Ross' [[Super Soldier Serum|Super Soldier Projects]] were going haywire once again.
[[File:GeneralGrellerMeetsRossBlonsky-DeletedScene.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross requests to search for [[Bruce Banner]]]]
While Greller confronted Ross over his decisions, Ross claimed that what they were dealing with was a potentially dangerous weapon if placed into the wrong hands, noting that they currently had no idea what Banner's intentions with Hulk were. Considering this, Greller gave Ross his permission to continue with his [[Strategic Operations Command Center]], noting that he would be under close scrutiny from this point onwards, as Ross and Blonsky had then left his office.{{Ref|TIHDS}}
[[File:Thaddeus Ross & Emil Blonsky.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross and [[Emil Blonsky]] discussing [[Hulk]]]]
Following their meeting with Greller, Ross and Blonsky walked down the corridors as they discussed the situation, as Blonsky noted that during his career with the [[United States Armed Forces]] he had seen several missions going terribly wrong when he and his unit were not given the correct information and were unprepared, but nothing like he had witnessed in Brazil, as Ross had looked down at Blonsky for suggesting that the failure of the mission should rest of his head.
[[File:TRossDebriefingBlonsky-Hallway.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross listening to [[Emil Blonsky]]'s arguments]]
Blonsky informed Ross that if they were planning on going after Hulk again, then he wanted to be a part of that mission. However, Ross was told that if Blonsky was to be sent out again, then he and his unit should be fully briefed about what to expect while tracking Banner; Blonsky noted that if their united was not prepared and they faced Hulk again, then a lot of professional soldiers would be terrified and they would inevitably lose Banner once again.{{Ref|TIH}}

====Discussion with Emil Blonsky====
[[File:Thaddeus Ross & Emil Blonsky.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross has his discussion with [[Emil Blonsky]]]]
{{Quote|But [[Hulk|he]] was so sure of what he was onto, he tested [[Super Soldier Serum|it]] on himself, and something went very wrong. Or it went very right. As far as I'm concerned, that man's whole body is property of the [[United States Army|U.S. Army]].|Thaddeus Ross to [[Emil Blonsky]]|The Incredible Hulk}}
Ross later met with [[Emil Blonsky]] once again as Ross had decided to disclose highly classified intel to Blonsky, noting that this information was highly sensitive to the [[United States Armed Forces]] as well as to Ross personally. Ross then commented that the Armed Forces had started a [[Project Rebirth|weapons development program]] that was started in [[World War II]], which Blonsky noted was the [[Super Soldier Serum]]. Ross confirmed that this is what he meant, noting that Blonsky's wording was an oversimplification of the work they had done.
[[File:GeneralRoss-Blonsky-SoldierChat.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross and Blonsky discussing [[Super Soldier Serum|Super Soldiers]]]]
Ross explained that he had restarted this program, which had led to the creation of [[Project Gamma Pulse]], as he noted while [[Washington, D.C.]] was attempting to give all the soldiers better weaponry, he was trying to make the soldiers themselves better. With Blonsky clearly intrigued by this, Ross went on to explain how [[Bruce Banner]]'s work with the project was in their early phases, and he had not known their intentions, believing it was for radiation resistance.
[[File:General Ross.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross explaining [[Bruce Banner]]'s past work]]
Ross then told Blonsky how Banner had been so certain about all his experiments with [[gamma radiation]] that he had tested it on himself, and something had gone terribly wrong, or very right depending on how he looked at it, resulting in the birth of [[Hulk]]. Ross noted that as far as he was concerned, Banner's entire body was the property of the Armed Forces. Blonsky had then questioned if Ross had been working to build weapons himself during all the experiments.
[[File:GeneralRoss-Blonsky-SuperSoldierChat.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross questions [[Emil Blonsky]]'s career path]]
As Blonsky asked about what Ross was working on, he admitted that they had also developed his version of the serum that seemed highly promising for all their work. Blonsky then questioned why Banner had escaped from the [[United States of America]] to hide out in [[Brazil]], to which Ross noted that Banner was simply a scientist and not a soldier like them and therefore could never understand their motivations for these experiments in creating super soldiers.
[[File:GeneralRossGivingEBlonskyAnOffer.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross offers to make [[Emil Blonsky]] stronger]]
Changing the subject, Ross asked Blonsky about his age, which Blonsky said was thirty-nine, as Ross noted how advancing age took a toll on the body of a soldier, as Blonsky noted that he intended to be a soldier for as long as he could be. When Blonsky noted how he wished he could put all his experience into the body he had ten years earlier, then he would have become an extraordinary soldier, to which Ross had then noted that something like this could be arranged.{{Ref|TIH}}

====Creating a Super-Soldier====
[[File:The-Incredible-Hulk-2008-Trailer-2-the-incredible-hulk-1750657-1275-540-1-.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross collecting their [[Super Soldier Serum]]]]
{{Quote|We're giving you a very low dose only. I need you sharp out there and disciplined. First sign of any side effect, we stop and you're off team until you straighten out. Agreed?|Thaddeus Ross to [[Emil Blonsky]]|The Incredible Hulk}}
General Ross and [[Emil Blonsky]] then came to an agreement and Blonsky accepted Ross's offer to be injected with an experimental version of the [[Super Soldier Serum]] that Ross had developed in order to match the strength of [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]] and be able to stand any chance at battling [[Hulk]]. Ross collected the Serum himself from a secure facility where [[Project Gamma Pulse]] had previously been conducting their experiments given Banner his powers.
[[File:GeneralRoss-WatchesOperation.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross watches [[Emil Blonsky]]'s experiments]]
Ross watched closely as Blonsky was injected with the Super Soldier Serum. Once their operation began, Ross had warned Blonsky that if anything went wrong then he would be taken off the team and kept in a hospital until he had recovered. The serum was injected directly in Blonsky's neck and spine, causing him considerable pain but also had increased his strength and agility to superhuman levels, allowing him to rejoin the unit and assist Ross in hunting down Hulk.{{Ref|TIH}}

====[[Battle at Culver University]]====
[[File:Ross and Sparr.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross leading their ambush on [[Bruce Banner]]]]
{{Quote|Alpha team, let [[Hulk|him]] have all of it.|Thaddeus Ross to [[SOCC]]|The Incredible Hulk}}
While the search for [[Bruce Banner]] continued, Thaddeus eventually gained intel from [[Leonard Samson]] that Banner was in [[Virginia]], since he had reconnected with [[Betty Ross]]. Upon learning this, Thaddeus gathered his unit back together, as they stormed into [[Culver University]] to capture Banner, who saw them coming at the last moment and fled to the building, as Thaddeus demanded to know who had let themselves be seen by him while [[Emil Blonsky]] gave chase, only for Thaddeus to tell Blonsky to stand down.
[[File:RossFamilyStandOff.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Thaddeus ordering [[Betty Ross]] to be taken away]]
As Thaddeus' men charged into the building after Banner, Thaddeus' armored truck was blocked by Betty, who then demanded that her father step out and speak to her. Eventually, Thaddeus obliged, while Betty begged him not to attempt to capture Banner, only for Thaddeus to then insist that she simply could not see the situation clearly. Before Thaddeus could have his daughter removed, one of Thaddeus' soldiers spotted Banner in an open corridor, where he became trapped.
[[File:GeneralRoss-WatchesTransformation.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross watches as [[Bruce Banner]] transforms]]
Thaddeus ordered his men not to engage, as they locked both the doors on either side before firing two gas canisters in the corridor with him. With the room filling with gas, Betty attempted to run to Banner's aid, before Thaddeus had ordered his men to bring her back. However, when Banner witnessed Betty being captured, his rage took over as Thaddeus witnessed his transformation into [[Hulk]]. While Thaddeus witnessed the change, he commented to himself that Betty would understand.
[[File:TIH-Thaddeus Ross (003).jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross ordering his soldiers to shoot at [[Hulk]]]]
As Hulk smashed his way free and roared at all the soldiers, Thaddeus ordered his unit to give him all they had. Thaddeus then watched on as his men fired their guns at Hulk, only for the bullets to simply bounce off his skin, as Thaddeus then ordered their bigger guns to join the battle. However, this only resulted in Hulk furiously [[Battle at Culver University|smashing]] through all the [[Humvee]]s that came after him, proving that their standard soldiers did not stand a chance as Thaddeus ordered Blonsky to join the battle.
[[File:GeneralRoss-MyGodHesDoingIt.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross ordering [[Emil Blonsky]] to battle [[Hulk]]]]
Thaddeus had then watched on with amazement as Blonsky's new found strength and speed allowed himself to fight Hulk single-handedly, proving that the [[Super Soldier Serum]] had indeed worked. As Blonsky managed to gain Hulk's attention, Thaddeus then ordered him to bring Hulk towards their [[Stark Sonic Cannon]]s, which fired their sound waves that stopped Hulk in his tracks. However, Betty continued begging her father not to harm Hulk, as he had her removed.
[[File:GeneralRoss-WatchesKicking.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross witnesses [[Hulk]] cripple [[Emil Blonsky]]]]
Seeing Betty in distress once again focused on Hulk's attention, as he made a shield to block all the sound waves before destroying the Humvees. Seeing this, Thaddeus ordered their gunship to assist them. However, before their gunship arrived, Thaddeus then witnessed Blonsky challenge Hulk alone, as he ordered him to get back. Blonsky had ignored the order and stood up to Hulk, who proceeded to kick Blonsky across the field, breaking every bone in Blonsky's body.
[[File:Ross-TIH.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross watches as [[Hulk]] manages to escape]]
Thaddeus had ordered his men to get back as the gunship arrived, only to then realize too late that Betty had walked up to Hulk and was in the firing line. Before Thaddeus could do anything, the gunship fired down at Hulk, who threw his shield at it, causing it to crash and engulf Betty and Hulk in a fireball. Thaddeus then watched in horror while Hulk emerged from the flames with an unconscious Betty in his arms, as Hulk had furiously growled at Thaddeus before he escaped.{{Ref|TIH}}

====Meeting with Leonard Samson====
[[File:Ross Samson.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross asks [[Leonard Samson]] for information]]
{{Quote|You did the right thing, calling [[United States Armed Forces|us]]. I need to know where they're going. [[Betty Ross|She]]'ll be in incredible danger as long as she's with [[Hulk|him]]."<br>"From who? He protected her. You almost killed her.|Thaddeus Ross and [[Leonard Samson]]|The Incredible Hulk}}
Following [[Hulk]]'s escape, Ross and his unit had then gone to [[Leonard Samson]]'s home where they had searched for any possible evidence they could find about what [[Bruce Banner]]'s plans were. While he was there, Ross had spoken with Samson, claiming that he had done the right thing by calling him, before then asking where they were heading.
[[File:General-Ross-Leonard-Samson.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross getting insulted by [[Leonard Samson]]]]
However, Samson noted that the military had put [[Betty Ross]] in more danger than Hulk during the [[Battle at Culver University|battle]] at [[Culver University]]. Although Thaddeus had still insisted that his daughter's safety was always his main concern, Samson claimed that he was lying to him before claiming to not know where they were going. As Thaddeus noted that this meant that she was aiding a fugitive, Samson claimed to finally understand why Betty never talked about her father, as Thaddeus then left the house.{{Ref|TIH}}

====Aftermath of the Battle====
[[File:TRoss-LookingAtBlonksy.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross looking at [[Emil Blonsky]] in the hospital]]
{{Quote|We have glimpsed the back part of God and for our [[United States of America|nation]], and for our way of life I intend to put a harness around [[Hulk|it]], and history will say that here, at this moment, we confronted our fear.|Thaddeus Ross to [[Kathleen Sparr]]|The Incredible Hulk - Deleted Scene}}
In the wake of the battle, Ross went to a medical unit to check on the treatment of [[Emil Blonsky]], as Ross had then asked a doctor whether or not Blonsky would ever walk again following being brutally kicked across the field by [[Hulk]]. The doctor had explained that most of his bones basically crushed gravel, while also commenting that Blonsky's heart still refused to stop beating. Ross then looked at Blonsky in his hospital bed, shocked by the state that he was in.{{Ref|TIH}}
[[File:TRoss-DeletedSceneQuotingWriters1.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross gets his updates from [[Kathleen Sparr]]]]
Disappointed at the situation, Ross returned to the control room and smoked a cigar, until he was joined by [[Kathleen Sparr]] who updated him on the search for [[Bruce Banner]]. Ross had then noted that he knew that Sparr was still having flashbacks from their latest encounter with Hulk, as Sparr claimed that it was outside her training with the [[United States Armed Forces]], noting that Hulk did not have any agendas that they could combat, as it was nothing but a force of pure rage.
[[File:TRoss-DeletedSceneQuotingWriters2.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross discusses [[Hulk]]'s incredible powers]]
Lost in his own thoughts, Ross quoted a great writer who claims that in the clefts of rocks people could see the back part of God and tremble. Ross then told Sparr that there was no training that could prepare her for an encounter with Hulk as this was a new kind of power never before faced. He also stated that such an event was incredibly rare and people always feared this kind of power and it was up to them to stop trembling and step toward to face off against that power.
[[File:TRoss-DeletedSceneQuotingWriters3.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross and [[Kathleen Sparr]] refuse to give up]]
Turning around, Ross told Sparr that they had faced the back part of God, and for the [[United States of America]] he had intended to put his harness around that incredible new power, while he then claimed that history would remember them fondly for this. Ross then offered Sparr a final chance to walk away from this fight, but she claimed that she would never forgive herself for surrendering to this battle and leaving someone else to do it, as they both agreed to continue the hunt.{{Ref|TIHDS}}

===Round Three===
====Emil Blonsky's Return====
[[File:GeneralRoss-WatchesTheNews.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross attempts to track down [[Bruce Banner]]]]
{{Quote|Good to see you back on your feet, soldier."<br>"Thank you, sir.|Thaddeus Ross and [[Emil Blonsky]]|The Incredible Hulk}}
In need of information about [[Hulk]]'s movements, Ross obtained the [[World Security Council]]'s permission to extract data from [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]]'s systems. A few hours later, Ross had been confronted by [[Nick Fury]] himself. Ross had told Fury that he was not going to leave the safety of the world in his hands.{{Ref|TAPFBW6}} Despite the constant questioning from S.H.I.E.L.D., Ross remained clearly focused on his mission and continued to track down Banner, until [[Kathleen Sparr]] then pulled him away from his work with an update.
[[File:GeneralRoss-Blonskys-Recovery.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross learns of [[Emil Blonsky]]'s swift recovery]]
Much to Ross' surprise, [[Emil Blonsky]] managed to recover incredibly quickly from the wounds suffered in the battle with [[Hulk]], with his bones all managing to repair themselves in a matter of hours due to the [[Super Soldier Serum]]. Ross asked Blonsky what he wanted to do now he was recovered, as he volunteered to under go the procedure again to increase his strength so that he might have another chance of fighting and even possibly defeating Hulk, as Ross agreed.
[[File:IncredibleHulk USAF FIB 2.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross giving his briefing about [[Bruce Banner]]]]
With Banner still on the run, Ross gathered the [[Strategic Operations Command Center]] together for the briefing on how they would track him down. However, despite Sparr noting how the [[FBI]] was assisting them in their search for Banner and [[Betty Ross]] by tracking their cell phones and credit cards, Ross got up and claimed Banner would not be foolish enough to use anything that could be tracked and that he was not trying to escape, but he would be attempting to find help.
[[File:Emil Blonsky & Thaddeus Ross.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross watches [[Emil Blonsky]]'s procedures]]
Eventually, using the information that they had gained from their first encounter with Banner in [[Brazil]], Sparr was able to track down his ally as [[Samuel Sterns]] who Banner was now attempting to meet at [[Grayburn College]]. Having gained a location on Banner, Ross agreed to allow Blonsky to be injected with more of the Super Soldier Serum, in order to make him strong enough to face Hulk again, as Ross stood by and closely watched their entire procedure on Blonsky's body.{{Ref|TIH}}

====Capturing Bruce Banner====
[[File:SOCC-TheIncredibleHulk002.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross and his squad flying to [[Bruce Banner]]]]
{{Quote|If you've taken it from me, I'm going to put you in a hole for the rest of your life.|Thaddeus Ross to [[Bruce Banner]]|The Incredible Hulk}}
With his [[Strategic Operations Command Center|team]] prepared for their mission, Ross rejoined them on the helicopter as they made their way to [[Grayburn College]] where [[Bruce Banner]] was attempting to cure himself of [[Hulk]].{{Ref|TIH}} Along the way, Ross listened as [[Kathleen Sparr]] briefed their team on how they would ambush Banner without actually engaging with him directly, only for [[Emil Blonsky]] to question what their plan was in case Banner was able to transform.
[[File:GeneralRossDeletedScene-HelicopterRide-TIH.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross discusses [[Emil Blonsky]]'s mental state]]
Hearing Blonsky's complaints, Ross then noted that if they failed to capture him without allowing him to transform, then they would have failed to learn from their previous mistakes, insisting that they needed to be ready to let him go. As Blonsky continued complaining, Sparr noted that the people of [[New York City]] would be in danger if Hulk was unleashed before questioning Blonsky's mental stability, only for Ross to then note that Blonsky might not be used in the field at all.{{Ref|TIHDS}}
[[File:GeneralRoss-CaptureOfBBanner.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross watches [[Emil Blonsky]]'s disobey him]]
Upon arriving at Grayburn College, Ross remained in their armored van with Sparr while Blonsky led his team inside and the snipers took their positions, finding Banner in with [[Samuel Sterns]] while they were discussing the [[gamma radiation]] in his blood. However, once snipers lined up their shot on Banner, Blonsky disobeyed Ross' direct orders as he charged upstairs to personally attack him, finding Banner just as he was shot with a tranquilizer dart and knocked unconscious.
[[File:General-Ross-Bruce-Banner-Captured.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross speaks to the captured [[Bruce Banner]]]]
With Banner having finally been captured, Ross then watched on as he was taken outside by his men, strapped onto a bed to keep him from escaping. Since they had found evidence that both Banner and Sterns had just completed their experiment to remove Hulk from his body, Ross stood over Banner and calmly warned that if he had managed to destroy Hulk for good, then Ross would ensure that Banner would spend the rest of his life locked inside a prison cell.
[[File:TRossSpeaksToBRoss-PostBannerCapture.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross' words are rejected by [[Betty Ross]]]]
While Banner was removed, [[Betty Ross]] left the college as Thaddeus had attempted to speak with her. However, Betty insisted that she would never forgive her father for what he had done to Banner. Although he tried to argue that Banner was a fugitive, Betty instead insisted that it was Thaddeus who had made Banner the fugitive to cover his failures and protect his own career in the [[United States Armed Forces]], noting she did not consider him her father before she furiously walked away, but not before Ross told her that it was only because she was his daughter that she was not being arrested along with Banner.{{Ref|TIH}}

====[[Duel of Harlem]]====
[[File:GeneralRoss-HelicopterCall-TIH.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Riss learning of [[Abomination]]'s attack]]
{{Quote|Use that thing, soldier. Give him some help!"<br>"Which one?"<br>"Help the [[Hulk|green one]], damn it! Which one do you think? Cut the [[Abomination|other one]] in half!|Thaddeus Ross and [[List of Minor Characters/Phase One#The Incredible Hulk|Gunner]]|The Incredible Hulk}}
Inside their helicopter, Thaddeus attempted to ignore [[Bruce Banner]] as he gently kissed [[Betty Ross]]' hands. However, just as they were leaving, Thaddeus had gotten a call from his [[Strategic Operations Command Center|men]] on the ground, claiming that [[Hulk]] was causing chaos in [[New York City]], much to Thaddeus' confusion as he looked over at Banner in their helicopter. Hearing the soldier's panic, Thaddeus ordered his pilot to turn the helicopter around.
[[File:BBannerTRossBRoss-HelicopterConfrontation.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross watches [[Abomination]]'s rampage]]
As the soldiers turned on their body-cams, Thaddeus then watched on in horror as the footage of [[Abomination]] causing utter destruction in the streets was broadcast, as Banner realized that this "Abomination" was [[Emil Blonsky]] who had forced [[Samuel Sterns]] to expose his body to more of the [[gamma radiation]], causing that transformation. Once Abomination slaughtered his men, Thaddeus tried to make a plan only for Banner to insist he be allowed to fight Abomination himself.
[[File:General-Ross-2nd-Hulk-Attack.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross and [[Bruce Banner]] discuss their plan]]
While the skeptical Thaddeus had listened closely, Banner claimed that he needed to be taken back so Hulk could [[Duel of Harlem|battle]] Abomination, believing he was the only one who stood a chance at defeating him. As Banner claimed that, while he could not fully control Hulk, he might be able to aim its rage at the correct target, which Thaddeus then questioned. When Banner noted that all three of them had all created Hulk, Thaddeus relented and ordered the pilot to land the helicopter.
[[File:TRossWatchesBBannerFalling.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross sees [[Hulk]] challenge [[Abomination]]]]
However, Banner insisted that they keep the helicopter out of harm's way, telling Thaddeus to open the back door as he prepared to jump out, unsure if he would even transform back into Hulk. Once Banner said his emotional goodbyes to Betty, Thaddeus then watched as he fell from the helicopter and landed in the streets, getting back to his feet as Hulk and furiously challenging Abomination to a fight. As the two began to fight, Thaddeus kept a close watch over the battle.
[[File:General-Ross-Gunman.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross' soldiers shooting at [[Abomination]]]]
Since it became clear that Abomination was far stronger than Hulk, Thaddeus ordered his gunner to begin shooting at Abomination, hoping that this would help. However, this only proved to enrage Abomination who was unaffected by the bullets and instead charged directly at the helicopter. Despite Hulk's best efforts to stop him, Abomination then tore the helicopter from the air, which caused it to crash land, while both Thaddeus and his daughter were still inside.
[[File:GeneralRoss-Injured-Crash.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross manages to survive a helicopter crash]]
With their helicopter having crash landed, Thaddeus and Betty found that they were the only survivors, as they painfully got back on their feet, finding that Hulk was still battling against Abomination. As the Rosses attempted to leave before Abomination could attack and kill them, their helicopter's fuel line burst into flames, causing a massive fireball. However, Hulk had witnessed this and, using his powerful clap, managed to extinguish the flames, saving their lives.
[[File:RossFamilyEscapingFromHelicopter.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross and [[Betty Ross]] escape the helicopter]]
With all the flames out, Thaddeus was helped out of the helicopter by his daughter, only for them to suddenly be spotted by Abomination, who was using a steel chain to beat Hulk into submission. Seeing the man who had helped transform him, Abomination then began furiously swinging the chain around his head in an attempt to kill the General, only for Hulk to return to the fight to save them, causing a small Earthquake that had knocked Abomination off his feet.
[[File:GeneralRossWatchesAbominationsDefeat.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross watches as [[Abomination]] is defeated]]
Using this brief distraction to his advantage, Hulk then wrapped the chain around Abomination's throat, attempting to chock him to death. Thaddeus and his daughter then watched on as Hulk beat Abomination into submission, even tearing out one of his bones, as continued strangling him until Betty stepped forward and begged Hulk to stop. Seeing the woman he loved, Hulk then calmed down as he tossed the defeated Abomination to the feet of Thaddeus.
[[File:GeneralRoss-WhiteLight.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross allows [[Hulk]] to make his escape]]
With Abomination finally defeated, the attention was then turned towards Hulk, as the [[United States Armed Forces]] surrounded the area, only for Thaddeus to order them to lower their weapons, as he knew that he now owed Hulk a debt for saving their lives and defeating Abomination. As Hulk looked down at Betty, more helicopters arrived and lit up the area, Thaddeus then simply allowed Hulk to make his escape, making absolutely no effort to recapture him.{{Ref|TIH}}

====Disastrous Press Conference====
[[File:General Thaddeus Ross.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross is enraged during a press conference]]
{{Quote|Following [[Hulk]] and the [[Abomination]]'s [[Duel of Harlem|destruction]] of [[Harlem]], Ross was criticized for what some called an 'unwarranted outburst' during a press conference.|[[Sharon Tazewell]]|Captain America: Brave New World}}
Ross spoke at a press conference following the fight between [[Hulk]] and [[Abomination]] to discuss the events that had transpired in [[Harlem]]. Ross was blamed for the damage done to the neighborhood, which enraged him, causing Ross to kick over the podium. Despite the negative response to his outburst from the public, Ross managed to twist the narrative in his favor by pinning the fault on the captured [[Samuel Sterns]], who created Abomination.{{Ref|CABNW}}

====Talk with Tony Stark====
[[File:TIH-Thaddeus Ross (012).JPG|{{AltFloat}}|Ross drinks and smokes alone in his despair]]
{{Quote|That [[Project Rebirth|Super Soldier program]] was put on ice for a reason. I've always felt that hardware was much more reliable."<br>"Stark. You always wear such nice suits.|[[Tony Stark]] and Thaddeus Ross|The Incredible Hulk}}
In the aftermath of the [[Duel of Harlem|battle]] and the humiliating defeat for Ross, the General drowned all his sorrows in bars, drinking and smoking. In order to try and save face, the [[World Security Council]] then informed [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]] that they wanted to make [[Emil Blonsky]], who was currently in Ross' custody, part of the [[Avengers Initiative]], blaming [[Hulk]] for the Harlem incident and keeping Blonsky's reputation intact.
[[File:Thaddeus Ross talks to Tony Stark.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross being visited by [[Tony Stark]] in the [[Demolished Bar|bar]]]]
S.H.I.E.L.D. agents [[Phil Coulson]] and [[Jasper Sitwell]], with knowledge of the events, sent [[Tony Stark]] to speak to Ross about the [[Avengers Initiative]], as their patsy to prevent Ross from letting Blonsky join the Avengers. Stark informed Ross that a [[Avengers|team]] was being put together. The talk ended up with Stark annoying Ross so much that Ross then refused to release Blonsky and tried to have Stark removed from the [[Demolished Bar|bar]]. In reply, Stark bought the bar and scheduled it for demolition.{{Ref|MOSTC}}

====Using Samuel Sterns====
{{Quote|Ross being Ross, he saw an opportunity. Instead of removing the [[Gamma Radiation|gamma]] from [[Samuel Sterns|Sterns]]' blood, he upped the dose. Made Sterns his own personal think tank. Creating technology and weapons for the [[United States|state]]."<br>"Holy shit. Why does Sterns go along with it?"<br>"[[Camp Echo One]] was the stick, I imagine a pardon was the carrot.|[[Sidewinder]] and [[Sam Wilson]]|Captain America: Brave New World}}
Ross discovered that in addition to [[Samuel Sterns]]' physical mutation, his mind had been enhanced from exposure to [[gamma radiation]] via [[Bruce Banner]]'s blood, making his brainpower incredibly higher than that of any other [[human]]. Seeing the potential of Sterns' intellect, Ross had him moved to [[Camp Echo One]] without a trial. Ross exposed Sterns to more gamma radiation to further increase his mental ability.

Ross forced Sterns to use his mind to solve solutions for him, including coming up with groundbreaking technology and weapons for the [[United States]]. Ross kept Sterns as his personal prisoner for years, under the watch of Warden [[Cooper (United States Army)|Cooper]], and kept his imprisonment a secret so that Sterns' mind could continue to benefit Ross' career. Ross managed to ensure Sterns' compliance by promising him that he would eventually pardon Sterns and give him his life back.{{Ref|CABNW}}

===Secretary of State===
====Position in Government====
[[File:Ross Whih.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross is promoted to the Secretary of State]]
{{Quote|[[2011|Five years ago]], I had a heart attack, and I dropped right in the middle of my backswing. Turned out it was the best round of my life because after thirteen hours of surgery and a triple bypass, I found something forty years in the [[United States Army|Army]] had never taught me. Perspective.|Thaddeus Ross to the [[Avengers]]|Captain America: Civil War}}
In [[2011]], while playing golf, Ross suffered from a heart attack which resulted in thirteen hours of surgery and a triple bypass.{{Ref|CACW}} By [[2016|April 2016]], General Ross was already retired from the [[United States Army]].{{Ref|WNF201}} He was then swiftly appointed as the [[United States]]' Secretary of State by President [[Matthew Ellis]], due to all of Ross' personal experience in dealing with the super-powered and highly dangerous individuals such as [[Hulk]], as well as [[Abomination]], throughout Ross' entire military career.{{Ref|WNF204}}
[[File:WHiH President and Ross.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|President [[Matthew Ellis]] comments on Ross]]
Once the [[United Nations]] of the world had begun to sought to impose greater accountability on the activities of super-heroes, including but not limited to the [[Avengers]], due to all the devastating events in [[Battle of New York|New York]], [[Battle at the Triskelion|Washington, D.C.]], [[Battle of Sokovia|Sokovia]], and [[Attack in Lagos|Lagos]], Ross took on an active role in trying to ensure the protection of the world from whom he had viewed as being super-powered vigilantes in the wake of their several battles. Ross oversaw the American government's implementation of the [[Sokovia Accords]] that would limit the actions undertaken by these super-powered individuals.{{Ref|CACW}}

====[[Sokovia Accords]]====
[[File:TRossBriefingTheAvengers1.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross having his meeting with the [[Avengers]]]]
{{Quote|For the past four years, you've operated with unlimited power and no supervision. That's an arrangement the governments of the [[Earth|world]] can no longer tolerate. But I think we have a solution: the [[Sokovia Accords]].|Thaddeus Ross to the [[Avengers]]|Captain America: Civil War}}
In [[2016|June 2016]], accompanied by [[Tony Stark]], Ross had visited the [[Avengers]] at the [[Avengers Compound]] to present them with the [[Sokovia Accords]]. Ross explained that there were no disagreements among the world's governments about whether the Avengers should all be considered heroes or vigilantes as the unlimited power with which they had operated could have no longer been tolerated since it was almost impossible to control.
[[File:TRossBriefingTheAvengers6.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross showing the footage of destruction]]
To prove his point, Ross showed his video footage of the destruction caused by the Avengers during the [[Battle of New York]], the [[Battle at the Triskelion]], the devastating [[Ultron Offensive]], and the [[Attack in Lagos]], in which [[Wanda Maximoff]] had inadvertently sent the bomb activated by [[Crossbones]] in a building occupied by several civilians who had died. Seeing the effect that the footage was having on Maximoff, [[Steve Rogers]] had asked Ross to end the presentation.
[[File:TRoss-OffersAvengersUltimatum.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross commenting on the [[Sokovia Accords]]]]
Ross then explained that since the [[Battle of Sokovia]] in which the city of [[Novi Grad]] had been completely destroyed, and many people were killed, the [[United States]] would sign their Sokovia Accords in order to put the Avengers into line, explaining that many other countries were planning to do the same. Ross explained how these Accords meant that the Avengers would only operate under the direct supervision of the [[United Nations]] in order to keep them under their close watch.
[[File:ThaddeusRoss-YouRetire.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross offers the [[Avengers]] a final ultimatum]]
While Rogers insisted they kept the world safe, Ross noted that they did not even know where [[Thor]] and [[Bruce Banner]] were, while [[James Rhodes]] had asked for more details about the contingency plans that were included with the Accords. As he left to give the Avengers some time to discuss their reactions to the Accords, Ross was then asked by [[Natasha Romanoff]] what would happen if they did not sign and he had simply explained that they would be forced to retire instead.{{Ref|CACW}}

====Captain America's Rebellion====
[[File:SecretaryRoss-ArrivingAtJCTC.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross confronts [[Tony Stark]] on the escape]]
{{Quote|[[Bucky Barnes|Barnes]] would have been eliminated in [[Romania]] if it wasn't for [[Steve Rogers|Rogers]]. There are dead people who would be alive now. Feel free to check my math.|Thaddeus Ross to [[Tony Stark]]|Captain America: Civil War}}
However, when the [[United Nations]] had been suddenly attacked with a bomb during the peace meetings regarding the [[Sokovia Accords]], it resulted in the deaths of several innocent people, including King [[T'Chaka]] of [[Wakanda]], all seemingly due to the terrorist actions of [[Winter Soldier]]. The former assassin was quickly caught and arrested, but broke out of his holding cell and went on the rampage when his programming was activated by [[Baron Zemo|Helmut Zemo]]. In the ensuing chaos, Zemo took the opportunity to escape, whilst [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]] chased down The Winter Soldier.
[[File:SecretaryRoss-WarningTStark.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross orders the capture of [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]]]]
Furious with what happened, Secretary Ross met with [[Tony Stark]] to confront him and demand that he bring Rogers, [[Sam Wilson|Falcon]] and Winter Soldier into justice. Upon hearing this, [[Natasha Romanoff]] questioned if Ross was willing to kill Captain America to catch Winter Soldier, which Ross noted he was. Stark then promised he would take their fugitives into custody within seventy-two hours, although Ross had still remained somewhat skeptical and gave Stark just thirty-six hours to deliver Rogers and Barnes.{{Ref|CACW}}

====Arresting the Avengers====
[[File:TRoss-MeetingTStark-CACW.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross threatens to have [[Tony Stark]] arrested]]
{{Quote|You seriously think I'm going to listen to you after that [[Battle at Leipzig-Halle Airport|fiasco]] in [[Leipzig-Halle Airport|Leipzig]]? You're lucky you're not in one of these [[Raft|cells]].|Thaddeus Ross to [[Tony Stark]]|Captain America: Civil War}}
In the wake of the [[Battle at Leipzig-Halle Airport]], Ross captured the majority of [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]]'s team and took them to the [[Raft]] where they had been thrown into individual cells. [[Tony Stark]] later flew to the Raft and was met by Ross, claiming that [[Helmut Zemo]] was to blame for the recent events, although Ross still remained furious about how bad the situation had become and then even threatened to have Stark arrested as well.
[[File:Civil War - 015478.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross watches [[Tony Stark]] talk to [[Sam Wilson]]]]
While Stark went to speak to their prisoners, Ross watched from the CCTV cameras as Stark was insulted by his former friends, with [[Clint Barton]] especially angry at the recent betrayal. While Stark had been speaking to [[Sam Wilson]] about the well-being of [[James Rhodes]] who had been badly injured, the audio feeds were then suddenly cut out during their conversation, which Ross had blamed on their technical team before realizing that Stark was most likely to blame for it all.
[[File:Civil War 102584.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross watches as [[Tony Stark]] leaves the [[Raft]]]]
Following his meeting with the [[Avengers]], Stark had then prepared to leave the Raft. As Ross walked Stark back to his helicopter, he asked what Wilson told him about [[Steve Rogers]] and all his plans, although Stark claimed it was nothing since Wilson had told him to go to hell, noting he was heading back to the [[Avengers Compound]] before taking off to investigate the situation further. As he left, Stark told Ross to call him any time, promising he would put Ross on hold.{{Ref|CACW}}

====[[Chase of Natasha Romanoff|Hunting Natasha Romanoff]]====
[[File:Secretary Ross (Black Widow).png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross leads his hunt for [[Natasha Romanoff]]]]
{{Quote|[[Natasha Romanoff]] is in violation of the [[Sokovia Accords]]. She assaulted the [[T'Challa|King]] of [[Wakanda]]. Make an example out of her.|Thaddeus Ross|Black Widow (film)}}
As his campaign against the [[Avengers]] continued, Ross had a second triple bypass surgery.{{Ref|BW}} Following [[Steve Rogers]]' escape, Ross suspected that [[Natasha Romanoff]] had assisted him.{{Ref|CACW}} He spoke to [[T'Challa]], who did not give a clear answer but left Ross feeling his suspicion of Romanoff was accurate. Ross then arranged a meeting with the [[World Security Council]] to ask for resources to capture Romanoff, where he and [[Hawley]] discussed Romanoff's history in depth, although Hawley refused to approve his request due to the lack of solid evidence.{{Ref|BWP1}}{{Ref|BWP2}}
[[File:Thaddeus Ross speaks to Natasha Romanoff.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross being contacted by [[Natasha Romanoff]]]]
Ross and his S.W.A.T. team eventually located Romanoff's tracker sending a signal from a train station in [[Albany]] and moved in to arrest her. Once they were inside, Ross was called on the phone by Romanoff. Ross told her to stop running from them as she was alone, since [[Clint Barton]], [[Sam Wilson]] and [[Scott Lang]] were currently in custody inside the [[Raft]], while Rogers was on the run. However, Ross was then promptly hung up on and discovered that Romanoff had tricked them with the tracker.{{Ref|BW}}

====Manipulating Rick Mason====
[[File:TRossWatchingOverRMason.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross forces [[Rick Mason]] to aid his mission]]
{{Quote|I am serving this very instant, right here in front of you, as I have my whole life. What I don't do is sell myself to the highest bidder, propping myself up like some debonair black market smuggler.|Thaddeus Ross to [[Rick Mason]]|Black Widow (film) - Deleted Scene}}
Seeking to arrest [[Natasha Romanoff]], Ross chose to target her contacts, seeking out anyone who was likely to be offering her support, as he tracked down [[Rick Mason]], putting pressure on him.{{Ref|BW}} Eventually, Ross' unit cornered Mason in his hotel room, as they waited for Romanoff to contact him, as they watched their conversation closely, with Romanoff and Mason agreeing to meet at a specific location with a van.
[[File:BlackWidowTeaserTrailer6.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross attempts to locate [[Natasha Romanoff]]]]
Ross sent his team to the location Romanoff agreed to meet at, taking Mason with him. Arriving at the location, Ross ordered his men turn the place upside down as they searched for Romanoff. As they searched for her tracker, Ross spoke with Mason, who asked Ross where he served during his time in the [[United States Armed Forces]], to which Ross insisted that he was actually still serving his country, unlike Mason.
[[File:TRossThreateningRMason-DS.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross demands [[Rick Mason]] explain himself]]
Irritated by this question, Ross had noted that he did not sell his services to the highest bidder, which he believed Mason did, claiming that Mason had been attempting to build a new false image of himself as a demonair smuggler for the black market. Ross had then warned that he would only give Mason five minutes to negotiate a plea deal for himself, which would only happen if he helped Ross to find a line on Romanoff.
[[File:TRossLearnsRomanoffEscaped-DS.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross learning [[Natasha Romanoff]] escaped]]
However, before Mason could consider cooperating with him, Ross was then interrupted by one of his agents, who explained that they had been unable to locate Romanoff. Ross was then told by the agent that they had found Romanoff's phone inside the café, which had been cleared by the bomb squad, with a note from her to Ross, telling Ross to come after her, which featured the [[Black Widows]]' logo and no further information.{{Ref|BWDS}}

====Natasha Romanoff's Surrender====
[[File:Secretary Thaddeus Ross.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross shows up to arrest [[Natasha Romanoff]]]]
{{Quote|Romanoff, what the hell happened here?"<br>"The [[Red Room]]."<br>"The [[Cold War]] spooks? They've been gone for years.|Thaddeus Ross and [[Natasha Romanoff]]|Black Widow (film)}}
Despite them having no leads on [[Natasha Romanoff]]'s location for some time, eventually Ross was alerted to the fact that her tracker had been turned on unexpectedly. As a result, Ross led his unit to track down and arrest Romanoff at her location, where they found her stood in the middle of a field, surrounded by destruction of the [[Red Room Academy]]. However, Romanoff managed to escaped from him.{{Ref|BW}}

====[[Escape from the Raft]]====
{{Quote|Tony, we have a problem."<br>"Ah, please hold."<br>"No. Don't–|Thaddeus Ross and [[Tony Stark]]|Captain America: Civil War}}
In the aftermath of the [[Avengers Civil War]], a couple of weeks after the [[Battle at the Hydra Siberian Facility]], [[Steve Rogers]] successfully broke into the [[Raft]] and helped the prisoners on the Raft to escape. Ross was notified of the ongoing escape, and contacted [[Tony Stark]] for help, only for Stark to fulfill his earlier promises and put Ross on hold and to ignore him much to his annoyance, as he attempted to demand Stark listen to him.{{Ref|CACW}} Ross then attempted to contact [[Everett Ross]] about the escape of the Raft's prisoners, but Everett did not answer him.{{Ref|AIWTHJ}}

====[[Infinity War]]====
[[File:Thaddeus Ross (2018).png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross continues working inside of his office]]
{{Quote|The [[Earth|world]]'s on fire, and you think all's forgiven?"<br>"I'm not looking for forgiveness. And I'm way past asking for permission. [[Earth]] just lost her [[Iron Man|best defender]]. So we're here to fight. And if you wanna stay in our way... we'll fight you, too.|Thaddeus Ross and [[Steve Rogers]]|Avengers: Infinity War}}
Because of the strain the events of the [[Battle at Leipzig-Halle Airport|Clash]] of the [[Avengers]] put on their own families, [[Scott Lang]] and [[Clint Barton]] both took deals from Ross that ended up with them being under house arrest, while the others involved with siding with [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]] during their clash still remained at large, despite Ross and his men continuing to hunt them down with the intention of finally bring them all to justice.
[[File:Thaddeus Ross & James Rhodes.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross has his meeting with [[James Rhodes]]]]
In [[2018|May 2018]], with the arrival of [[Thanos]]' [[Q-Ship]]s into [[New York City]], as well as the sudden disappearance of [[Vision]], Ross contacted [[James Rhodes]] at the [[Avengers Compound]] when it was found that Vision was rescued by three wanted criminals; Captain America, [[Black Widow]] and [[Sam Wilson|Falcon]]. When he and Rhodes had discussed Vision's disappearance, Rhodes claiming that their former allies had only become known as criminals because of Ross, which Ross had merely scoffed at.
[[File:Ross vs Cap.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross confronting the rest of the [[Avengers]]]]
As Ross and Rhodes talked, Rhodes noted that he had some second thoughts about the Accords, before revealing that Captain America and his team had arrived with Vision and [[Wanda Maximoff]]. Upon seeing their arrival, Ross confronted Rogers who claimed they were there to assist after [[Tony Stark]] had vanished. Ross then ordered Rhodes to arrest the fugitives, but Rhodes instead terminated their connection, which earned him Ross' anger and a court-martial as a result.{{Ref|AIW}}
[[File:Maria Hill (Avengers Endgame).png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross shows respect at [[Tony Stark]]'s funeral]]
Despite the Avengers' best efforts, Thanos managed to obtain all six of the [[Infinity Stones]] and caused the [[Snap]], which killed Ross among trillions of others, including Ross' [[Betty Ross|daughter]].{{Ref|AEScript}} However, in [[2023|five years]] following the Snap, [[Hulk]] then caused the [[Blip]] and resurrected them. Ross had later attended the funeral of [[Tony Stark]], who had given his life to defeat [[Thanos/Cosmic Time Heist|Thanos]], with Ross standing beside [[Maria Hill]], while they had watched Stark's [[Arc Reactor]] being set adrift into the lake.{{Ref|AE}}

====Enhanced Humans Act====
In [[2024]], Ross ordered Major [[Donavan]] to mark as classified any information relating to the [[Enhanced Humans Act]].{{Ref|TFaTWSCS}}

====Saved by Samuel Sterns====
{{Quote|Because I was dying, goddamn it! Because my heart was failing! No one could figure it out until [[Samuel Sterns|he]] did. [[Gamma Radiation Pills|These things]] have kept me alive. And in return, I gave him hope that he might get his life back. He got a lab to do the work. I even tried to get him moved but–"<br>"But you couldn't risk losing the pills.|Thaddeus Ross and [[Sam Wilson]]|Captain America: Brave New World}}
With his heart condition worsening, Ross was dying, so he sought help from various doctors, but to no success. Desperate to stay alive long enough so that he could show his [[Betty Ross|daughter]] that he had changed for the better and hopefully repair their relationship, Ross went to [[Samuel Sterns]] for help. Sterns was provided a lab at [[Camp Echo One]] from Ross, and was able to figure out how to save his life.

Ross was given [[Gamma Radiation Pills|pills]] that had been developed by Sterns, which he was required to take three times a day, which healed his heart. Ross was grateful for Sterns saving his life and wanted to have him moved out of Camp Echo One, but ultimately, Ross was too scared about losing the pills, so he kept Sterns locked up with the hope that he might be released.{{Ref|CABNW}}

===President of the United States===
====First Hundred Days====
[[File:Ross CABNW first scene.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross asks if his [[Betty Ross|daughter]] had reached out]]
{{Quote|Tonight, [[United States of America|America]] has spoken in one of the most important elections of our lifetimes. We've recognized the urgency of this moment. From the [[Snap|disappearance of half of mankind]] to the [[emergence]] of a [[Tiamut the Communicator|Celestial mass]] in the {{WPS|Indian Ocean}}, the threats we face show no signs of slowing down. But the only way we can overcome them is together!|Thaddeus Ross|Captain America: Brave New World}} 
In [[2026]], Ross decided to run for President of the [[United States]], in which he was advised to shave his mustache to better his chances. Using [[Samuel Sterns]] to assist his campaign, which focused on the whole [[Earth|world]] working together, Ross won the election. Before giving his speech, Ross asked one of his staff members if they had heard from his [[Betty Ross|daughter]], but she had not reached out, which disappointed Ross.
[[File:Ross Together.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross gives a speech following his victory]]
Ross took one of his [[Gamma Radiation Pills|pills]] and stepped out to a crowd of his supporters to give his acceptance speech. Ross stated that the election was one of the most important due to the rising threats over the last few years, including the [[Blip]] and the [[Emergence]]. Continuing from this, Ross felt that the threats were not slowing down and that the only way they could be overcome was if they all worked together. Following his inauguration, Ross hired [[Ruth Bat-Seraph]], a former [[Red Room]] assassin, as his security advisor.
[[File:Leila and Ross.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross talks about changing for his [[Betty Ross|daughter]]]]
In order to prove that he was changing for the better, Ross began working with [[Captain America]]. On [[2027|April 15, 2027]], [[adamantium]] was stolen from the [[Japan]]ese by [[SERPENT]], so Ross deployed Captain America to retrieve it. Meanwhile, Ross went to visit his [[Karen Lee Ross|wife]]'s grave, where he spoke to [[Leila Taylor]] about his daughter still not speaking with him and the importance of his treaty working. Ross was contacted and informed that the adamantium had been successfully [[Skirmish at Catedral de Santo Ramos|recovered]].{{Ref|CABNW}}

====Meeting with Sam Wilson====
[[File:Wilson and Ross.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross has a meeting with [[Sam Wilson]]]]
{{Quote|You and I haven't always agreed on how much latitude enhanced individuals deserve. But what you've accomplished has given me reason to reconsider. Which is why I want you, Captain America, to help me rebuild the [[Avengers]].|Thaddeus Ross to [[Sam Wilson]]|Captain America: Brave New World}}
Following the [[Skirmish at Catedral de Santo Ramos|recovery]] of the [[adamantium]], Ross called [[Sam Wilson]] and invited him and [[Joaquín Torres]] to attend his [[Celestial Island World Summit|summit]] at the [[White House]]. Wilson accepted, under the condition that [[Isaiah Bradley]] could also attend. Before the summit, Ross had Wilson brought to the Oval Office.
[[File:Captain America Brave New World Teaser Trailer (15).png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross suggests rebuilding the [[Avengers]]]]
Ross thanked Wilson for retrieving the adamantium, stating that it saved the treaty he was working on. Ross then noted that while he did not always agree with superheroes, he had a change of mind due to Wilson's work as Captain America, and revealed his desire to rebuild the [[Avengers]] with him. Wilson was confused about Ross' proposal, so he clarified that it was what the [[United States|country]] needed. Wilson asked about what would happen if they disagreed on how to manage a situation, Ross claimed that they would work it out together.
[[File:Sam and President Ross Press.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross pictured with [[Sam Wilson]] and [[Ozaki]]]]
Ross ended his meeting with Wilson, telling him to think on his proposal, and then exited the room and greeted Prime Minister [[Ozaki]]. Ross then introduced Wilson to Ozaki, and the three of them took a picture together. Ross told Wilson to work with him so that they could show the [[Earth|world]] a better way forward. Ross came across Bradley and expressed his disgust at what had happened to him. Ross asked Bradley to meet with him after the summit to discuss mending his past.{{Ref|CABNW}}

====[[Celestial Island World Summit]]====
[[File:Ross reveals adamantium.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross reveals [[adamantium]] at the [[Celestial Island World Summit|summit]]]]
{{Quote|What we do next with this discovery will determine how history judges us. If we ratify this treaty, together we can produce enough [[adamantium]] to fairly and equitably distribute it around the [[Earth|world]]. No nation left behind.|Thaddeus Ross|Captain America: Brave New World}}
Ross stood before his guests and commenced the [[Celestial Island World Summit|summit]], where he detailed the events following the [[Emergence]] that led to the discovery of [[adamantium]]. Ross publicly thanked [[Sam Wilson]] and [[Joaquín Torres]] for [[Skirmish at Catedral de Santo Ramos|recovering]] the adamantium and stated that his treaty would allow adamantium to be fairly distributed around the [[Earth|world]].
[[File:Captain America Brave New World Teaser Trailer (45).png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross is suddenly attacked by [[Isaiah Bradley]]]]
Suddenly, [[Isaiah Bradley]] attacked an agent and stole his gun, which he used to shoot at Ross. Bradley missed, shooting the glass instead, and Ross dropped to the floor. The room erupted into chaos as more people began attacking, including another agent who ran at Ross, but was knocked out with a single punch from the President. [[Leila Taylor]] rushed to help Ross and escorted him to safety. The situation was dealt with, and the attackers, including Bradley were all arrested.{{Ref|CABNW}}

====Aftermath of the Ambush====
[[File:Captain America Brave New World Teaser Trailer (60).png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross discusses the assassination attempt]]
{{Quote|Sir, you invited me here to work together, so let's work together."<br>"I'm afraid that off expired when your [[Isaiah Bradley|friend]] tried to kill me. Sam, you shouldn't even be in these situations, you're not [[Steve Rogers]].|[[Sam Wilson]] and Thaddeus Ross|Captain America: Brave New World}}
Ross was taken to the {{WPS|Presidential Emergency Operations Center|PEOC}} and joined by his staff, who discussed the situation. They were interrupted when [[Sam Wilson]] forced his way inside, so Ross ordered everyone to leave so he could talk with Wilson. The two were joined by [[Ruth Bat-Seraph]], so Wilson asked for privacy, but Ross stated that she would stay in the room. Wilson and Bat-Seraph began arguing about [[Isaiah Bradley]]'s attack, so Ross stopped them.
[[File:Captain America Brave New World Teaser Trailer (87).png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross tells [[Sam Wilson]] his offer has expired]]
Bat-Seraph recounted the events that transpired to figure out what they knew, and Wilson defended Bradley. Wilson wanted to look into the attack, but Ross felt that Wilson personally investigating his own friend would be create poor optics. Wilson reminded Ross of his proposal to work together, but Ross replied that the offer was now expired. Ross told Wilson that should not be involved as he was not [[Steve Rogers]]. Ross authorized Bat-Seraph to lead the investigation and dismissed Wilson.{{Ref|CABNW}}

====Deliberating with World Leaders====
[[File:Ross speaks with India and France.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross discusses the treaty with the leaders]]
{{Quote|This treaty is too important to let it fall apart now. We made a promise to our people. We made a promise to the [[Earth|world]]. We must prevail."<br>"We'll need [[Japan]] to proceed.|Thaddeus Ross and [[Kapur]]|Captain America: Brave New World}}
Ross contacted [[Cooper (United States Army)|Cooper]] to check on the status of [[Samuel Sterns]]. Cooper told Ross that he had visual of Sterns imprisoned in his cell. Ross then spoke with Prime Minister [[Kapur]] and the President of [[France]], who voiced doubt in Ross' leadership and his treaty. Ross attempted to assure the other leaders that they had the situation under control and just required their patience.
[[File:Ross leaves the PEOC.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross informs [[Leila Taylor]] that he is leaving]]
The French President questioned Ross' request for patience, referring to him by his old nickname, "[[Hulk]] Hunter," but Ross tried to distance himself from that moniker. Ross insisted upon the importance of the treaty, but he was informed that [[Ozaki]] was not on board. Ross promised to speak with Ozaki, and the other leaders agreed to wait, although threatening to take measures into their own hands if the treaty fell through. Ross decided to leave the {{WPS|Presidential Emergency Operations Center|PEOC}}, which [[Leila Taylor]] questioned, but he stated that hiding made him look weak.{{Ref|CABNW}}

====Visit to Japan====
[[File:Taylor and Ross.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross and [[Leila Taylor]] discuss the situation]]
{{Quote|Mr. President, this is extremely dangerous. If a war breaks out..."<br>"I was a wartime general. Now I'm a wartime president.|[[Leila Taylor]] and Thaddeus Ross|Captain America: Brave New World}}
Ross headed for [[Japan]] in [[Air Force One]], and during the flight he was joined by [[Leila Taylor]], so he asked for her thoughts. Taylor answered that the person who orchestrated the [[Attack on President Ross|attack]] was still out there and it was still dangerous for him to be traveling, but Ross emphasized the importance of the treaty working. 
[[File:Ross called by Leader.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross learns [[Samuel Sterns]] is responsible]]
Ross then asked about [[Sam Wilson]]'s status, so Taylor informed him that Wilson and [[Joaquín Torres]] had gone off-grid. Ross ordered Taylor to send agents to bring them in. Ross was then called by Warden [[Cooper (United States Army)|Cooper]], only to hear Cooper be killed. [[Samuel Sterns]] picked up the phone and revealed that he was behind the attacks as revenge for his imprisonment. Sterns then told Ross that he was going to show everyone who Ross truly was, which would make his [[Betty Ross|daughter]] despise him more.
[[File:Ross accused by Ozaki.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross is accused by Prime Minister [[Ozaki]]]]
Ross contacted [[Ruth Bat-Seraph]] and told her to get to [[Camp Echo One]], as it had become compromised. Landing in Japan, Ross met with [[Ozaki]] and discussed upholding the treaty. Ross was shocked when Ozaki accused him of being responsible for the theft of the [[adamantium]], which was supported by verified intel that he showed Ross. Certain that this was not to be true, Ross told Ozaki that he was being played, but Ozaki did not believe Ross and refused to uphold the treaty.
[[File:BNW TV Spot (6).png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross decides to claim all the [[adamantium]]]]
Ozaki's claims were confirmed to be true, so Ross wanted to be alone, but his staff informed him that Ozaki had moved his navy towards [[Celestial Island]] to claim all of the adamantium. His staff argued about their next course of action, causing Ross to snap and hit the table, cracking it slightly. Ross decided to advance on Celestial Island as well, stating that if only one country would control adamantium, it would be them. Ross told Taylor that he wanted to be at Celestial Island within the hour. Taylor was worried about a war breaking out, but Ross was not fazed by the prospect.{{Ref|CABNW}}

====Confronted by Sam Wilson====
[[File:Wartime President Ross.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross advances towards [[Celestial Island]]]]
{{Quote|After your friend the [[Hulk]] and the [[Abomination]] [[Duel of Harlem|destroyed]] [[Harlem]], someone had to take the fall. [[Leader|Sterns]] was just... collateral damage.|Thaddeus Ross to [[Sam Wilson]]|Captain America: Brave New World}}
Ross boarded the [[USS Milius]] and headed for [[Celestial Island]] to beat [[Japan]]. [[Ruth Bat-Seraph]] arrived on the ship with [[Sam Wilson]] and [[Joaquín Torres]], so Ross questioned their presence, having ordered them not to get involved. Bat-Seraph attempted to explain, but Ross cut her off, stating that she failed her job. Wilson stepped in and revealed he was aware of [[Samuel Sterns]], so Ross went to speak privately with him.
[[File:CABNW Ross and Sam.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross tells [[Sam Wilson]] about [[Samuel Sterns]]]]
The two entered another room, where Wilson explained how Sterns was pitting Ross against [[Ozaki]] to cause a war to break out. Ross questioned how Sterns was capable of doing so, so Wilson revealed it was through mind control technology, and wondered if Ross had been effected showing a file with his data on it. Ross deflected Wilson's questioning until he revealed that he was dying and Sterns saved his life and that he still needed to repair his relationship with his [[Betty Ross|daughter]]. Wilson claimed that Ross still could but needed to do the right thing at that moment, otherwise they would play into Sterns' plans of inciting a war.{{Ref|CABNW}}

====[[Battle of Celestial Island]]====
[[File:Ross despatches Cap and Falcon.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross sends out [[Captain America]] and [[Falcon]]]]
{{Quote|You poisoned me!"<br>"Stop taking the [[Gamma Radiation Pills|pills]] then. But we both know you won't. Give me what I want. Stop fighting it.|Thaddeus Ross and [[Leader]]|Captain America: Brave New World}}
They were interrupted and informed that two pilots had gone rogue and attacked the [[Japan]]ese fleet. Desperate to get [[Whiskey]] and [[Jackal]] out of the air, Ross deployed [[Captain America]] and [[Falcon]] to deal with the situation. Unable to call off their pilots, the Japanese opened fire upon the [[USS Milius]], forcing Ross to fire intercepting missiles.
[[File:Brave New World (13).png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross nearly succumbs to [[Leader]]'s plans]]
Ross attempted to explain the situation to [[Ozaki]], but when Ozaki questioned who the pilots were taking orders from, Ross did not answer. Ross started to feel unwell and then heard [[Samuel Sterns]] speaking to him. Ross moved to the hallway, continuing to feel worse. Ross realized that Sterns had poisoned him, and Sterns told him to give in to his rage. Ross started to transform, but was stopped when [[Leila Taylor]] told him the pilots had been neutralized. Ross calmed down and went to fix the situation with Ozaki.{{Ref|CABNW}}

====[[Duel of Washington, D.C.|Becoming Red Hulk]]====
[[File:Ross speaks with Betty.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross' call is finally accepted by his [[Betty Ross|daughter]]]]
{{Quote|Ross. We both know you can take me out with one punch, but I don't think you wanna do that. I know you've done some terrible things. Now, I might be crazy... but I think you're trying to change. Now's the time to prove it to the [[Earth|world]]. Prove it to [[Betty Ross|Betty]].|[[Captain America]] to Red Hulk|Captain America: Brave New World}}
With the conflict resolved, Ross returned to [[Washington, D.C.]], where Ross waited inside the [[White House]] while his team swept the area outside. Once [[Leila Taylor]] informed him they were clear, Ross decided to call his [[Betty Ross|daughter]], and was surprised when she answered. Ross told his daughter that he was trying to change and asked her to join him on a walk to see the cherry blossoms, which she agreed to.
[[File:Ross press conference.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross' secrets are exposed by [[Leader]]]]
Ross went outside, where he gave a press conference to announce that his treaty would finally be signed. As Ross took questions, he was asked about the recent tensions with [[Japan]], all of which he dismissed as fabrications. Ross was then informed that [[Samuel Sterns]] had turned himself in and revealed that Ross promised him a pardon in exchange for his work. Ross denied the report, but the speakers suddenly played the phone conversation between Ross and Sterns which confirmed the truth.
[[File:Red Hulk First Front Look.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ross gives in to his rage and transforms]]
The [[United States Secret Service|Secret Service]] surrounded Ross and tried to move him away, but Ross resisted them, wanting to explain himself to the public. Taylor told Ross she could not let him, which angered him, and Ross then started to lose control as he dropped to the ground and began to transform into Red Hulk. Consumed with rage and no longer in control, Red Hulk began to attack, so the Secret Service opened fire upon him, which did had no effect and only angered him more.
[[File:PresidentRedHulk.png|{{AltFloat}}|Red Hulk goes on a destructive rampage]]
[[Captain America]] arrived and hit Red Hulk with his [[Captain America's Shield|shield]], stopping him from attacking the Secret Service. Red Hulk and Captain America began to fight, with Red Hulk destroying the White House in the process. On the rooftop, Red Hulk grabbed the flagpole and swung it at a group of soldiers, but Captain America saved them. Two drones arrived and opened fire, but Red Hulk knocked one down, grabbed it, and threw it at the other drone, destroying both of them.
[[File:Red Hulk.png|{{AltFloat}}|Red Hulk stands on a burning [[White House]]]]
Standing atop the destroyed White House, Red Hulk roared at Captain America while he was in the sky. Captain America then hit Red Hulk in the chest with blades from his [[EXO-7 Falcon|wings]], which angered him. Red Hulk lunged after Captain America and chased him to Hains Point, destroying part of the [[Washington Monument]] along the way. Captain America attempted to calm Red Hulk down, reminding him of the cherry blossoms, but it did not work as Red Hulk pulled a blade out of his chest.
[[File:Red Hulk v Captain America.png|{{AltFloat}}|Red Hulk furiously fights [[Captain America]]]]
Red Hulk then charged at Captain America, but was blinded by [[Redwing]], allowing Captain America to jump over him and slash his back. Red Hulk destroyed one of the Redwing drones and threw a car at Captain America, but he was able to dodge it. As Captain America braced himself under his shield and wings, Red Hulk repeatedly pummelled him to break through. Red Hulk destroyed the other Redwing drone and managed to grab Captain America by his wing when he went to fly away.
[[File:Red Hulk head crush.png|{{AltFloat}}|Red Hulk attempts to kill [[Captain America]]]]
Captain America threw his shield to hit Red Hulk, who caught it and slammed it into the ground. Red Hulk ripped off one of Captain America's wings and started to crush his helmet to kill him, only to be stopped when Captain America kicked in one of his blades that was still piercing Red Hulk's side. Captain America got some distance from Red Hulk, who then jumped at him to attack, however, Captain America used his remaining wing that was charged up to stab Red Hulk, creating a massive burst of energy.
[[File:Ross transforms back.png|{{AltFloat}}|Red Hulk transforms back after the battle]]
Red Hulk was knocked back and buried under rubble, but he soon got back up. Red Hulk and Captain America slowly approached each other, and before the fight could continue, Captain America tried again to get through to Red Hulk. Captain America told Red Hulk to prove that he was trying to change for his [[Betty Ross|daughter]], and after holding a cherry blossom petal in his hand, Red Hulk managed to calm down and reverted back to Ross. EMTs arrived at the scene and took Ross to help him.{{Ref|CABNW}}

====Imprisoned at the Raft====
[[File:Ross in the Raft.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross is imprisoned inside of the [[Raft]]]]
{{Quote|But I have to say, it wasn't nothing to see you take full responsibility for your actions. Give up your office. Accept your sentence."<br>"I had to let the [[United States|country]] move on.|[[Sam Wilson]] and Thaddeus Ross|Captain America: Brave New World}}
Following his [[Duel of Washington, D.C.|incident]] as Red Hulk, Ross decided to take accountability for his actions and stepped down as President of the [[United States]] and accepted his sentence, which had him imprisoned in the [[Raft]]. [[Sam Wilson]] went to visit Ross, and the two discussed the conditions of the cell, as well as [[Isaiah Bradley]]'s release.
[[File:Thaddeus Ross in the Raft.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross and [[Sam Wilson]] discuss his actions]]
Wilson explained to Ross that the [[Gamma Radiation Pills|pills]] [[Samuel Sterns]] made were dosed with [[gamma radiation]], and built up in his body over the years which led to him becoming Red Hulk, which was why he had to be kept contained inside the Raft. Wilson commended Ross on taking responsibility, and Ross stated that he had to allow the country to move on. Wilson also informed Ross that the treaty was upheld by [[Japan]] and the United States, and was dubbed the [[Ozaki-Ross Accords]].
[[File:Ross sees Betty.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ross is finally reunited with his [[Betty Ross|daughter]]]]
Ross questioned Wilson's visit, seeing as they opposed each other, but Wilson stated that they needed to see the good in each other and he wanted to make sure Ross was doing well. Wilson told Ross that he had to leave, but revealed that there was another visitor to see him. Ross got up and discovered his [[Betty Ross|daughter]] had come to see him. Ross told her that he needed to reschedule their walk, but she replied that they could just talk for a while instead, which made both of them happy, now finally reunited.{{Ref|CABNW}}

==Powers and Abilities==
===Powers===
{{Rewrite|Manual of Style}}
{{Quote|And to recall that our last President turned into a bright red-superhuman monster who nearly [[Duel of Washington, D.C.|destroyed]] this [[Washington, D.C.|city]].|[[Valentina Allegra de Fontaine]] to [[United States Congress]]|Thunderbolts*}}
*'''Artificially Enhanced Physiology''': When Ross developed a heart condition, he turned to [[Samuel Sterns]]' help in developing a medicine to save his life, which Sterns was able to do. However, unknown to Ross, Sterns laced the pills with [[gamma radiation]], which Sterns somehow activated after his [[Attack on President Ross|attempt on Ross' life]] failed, transforming Ross into a being called Red Hulk.
**'''Transformation''': Similar to Bruce Banner, Ross' transformation was triggered by intense moments of stress, but his first transformation was triggered by [[Leader]] activating the [[gamma radiation]] in Ross' body. When [[Captain America]] calmed Ross down, he was able to revert back to human form. 
***'''Superhuman Strength''': Red Hulk possesses immense levels of superhuman strength, as he was easily capable of throwing cars, crushing and throwing a helicopter, smashing through trees, destroying most of the White House by clapping his hands together and leaping huge distances across Washington. A single punch caused serious stress on Captain America's Vibranium Wings due to the sheer amount of kinetic energy being absorbed, rag-dolling and launching Sam across the battlefield several times even when his wings and shield absorbed much of the impact. After a short but intense 1-on-1 battle with Captain America, Red Hulk managed to tear off one of his wings and crush his helmet. The kinetic force absorbed from Red Hulk's punches was powerful enough to decimate much of the surrounding street in a kinetic explosion, destroying what was left of Captain America's wings.
***'''Superhuman Durability''': Red Hulk possesses immense levels of superhuman durability. Bullets from handguns and miniguns simply bounce off his skin and lasers from Redwing Drones barely affect him. His skin can be pierced by Vibranium weapons, however these wounds did not inflict lasting damage, doing little more than angering him.  Red Hulk also withstood a kinetic explosion at point-blank rage that was powered by his own attacks without suffering any notable damage.
***'''Superhuman Speed''': Red Hulk was able to chase Captain America through Washington DC, able to keep up with and eventually catch Sam despite him flying at high speed. He also caught him off guard with a leaping attack that launched him through the White House. 
***'''Superhuman Agility''': Red Hulk can leap huge distances with a single jump. He was able to catch Captain America mid-flight with a leaping attack. He was also able to keep up with and eventually catch Sam after chasing him through Washington despite Sam flying at high speeds and flying through a dense forest to slow him down.
***'''Superhuman Stamina''': Red Hulk was able to fight off military forces and Captain America without showing any signs of exhaustion. Even after being caught in a kinetic explosion that decimated the streets, Red Hulk was still able to fight, forcing Sam to try to reason with him. 
***'''Superhuman Reflexes''': Red Hulk's reflexes are fast enough that he could destroy two Redwing drones with his fists and could catch Captain America's shield with one hand while attempting to crush the Vibranium wings with his other hand.
***'''Regenerative Healing Factor''': Red Hulk appears to have a healing factor, as wounds from Vibranium daggers and wings that pierced his skin had no lasting effect. He also quickly recovered from a kinetic explosion that destroyed the streets and launched a car on top of him.
***'''Heat Generation''': [[File:Red Hulk throws a flaming car.png|thumb|250px|Red Hulk igniting a car]] Red Hulk's body emits gamma radiation that raises his body temperature with rage, allowing him to generate extreme levels of heat from his skin as he gets angrier. During his first transformation, his skin began to boil and steam, incinerating much of his clothing and scorching the floor. When he crashed into the White House after leaping into Sam, much of the building immediately caught fire. When attacking Captain America, the latter's Vibranium wings would repeatedly scorch and generate embers as he collided into obstacles, burning intensely when Red Hulk ripped off his left wing. Most notably, a car immediately burst into flames when Red Hulk grabbed it by its fuel tank, essentially turning it into a fireball when he hurled it at Wilson.

===Abilities===
<!-- The power list and levels has been carefully reviewed and approved by Wiki-Projects with the media released as of the end of 2021. DO NOT MAKE arbitrary changes to them or it may lead to blocks. -->
{{Quote|Secretary Ross has a Congressional Medal of Honor, which is one more than you have.|[[War Machine]] to [[Sam Wilson|Falcon]]|Captain America: Civil War}}
*'''Master Tactician''': [[File:Thaddeus Ross (Black Widow).png|thumb|250px|Ross leading his hunt on [[Natasha Romanoff]]]] As a general, he is in a leadership position in the military and trained to command people. Ross coordinated his [[Strategic Operations Command Center|unit]] on how to attack [[Hulk]] without being present personally. He also knows how to find allies to help his cause who can provide the right equipment and personnel. Ross knows when to change tactics based on the situation; he made [[Bruce Banner]], a perceived foe, an ally for him to battle [[Emil Blonsky]].
*'''Master Combatant''': As a general with decades of military experience, Ross is highly skilled in combat. Despite his advanced age, he easily knocked out a gunman with one punch during the attempt on his life at the [[White House]]. Even after his transformation into Red Hulk, despite being in a state of intense rage, Ross still retained some level of combat awareness. He targeted [[Sam Wilson]]'s [[vibranium]] [[EXO-7 Falcon|wings]] when Wilson tried to retreat after absorbing a barrage of punches, tearing his left wing off and leaving him almost helpless. He also anticipated Wilson's attempt to free himself with a ricochet shield throw attack, swiftly catching the shield and slamming it into the ground.

